{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`pi-vimmode` replaces Pi's prompt editor with `VimEditor`, a `CustomEditor` subclass. The current implementation works, but `VimEditor` now owns multiple responsibilities: Pi input delegation, modal state, normal/visual key dispatch, register updates, status rendering, visual render setup, terminal cursor hints, and cursor restoration through Pi movement keys. The project already has useful seams: `src/commands.ts` parses finite normal-mode grammar and `src/buffer.ts` contains pure text/register"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Keep `VimEditor` as the Pi-facing `CustomEditor` implementation while slimming it to adapter duties."}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 24", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### Decision: Use `VimEditor` as the Pi adapter shell `VimEditor` SHALL remain the class constructed by `src/index.ts` and still extend `CustomEditor`. It will collect editor snapshots, call the modal module, apply returned effects, bridge rendering/status, and preserve lifecycle-sensitive behavior such as cursor reset."}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_decision_use_vimeditor_as_the_pi_adapter_shell", "label": "Decision: Use VimEditor as the Pi adapter shell", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 26", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`VimEditor` SHALL remain the class constructed by `src/index.ts` and still extend `CustomEditor`. It will collect editor snapshots, call the modal module, apply returned effects, bridge rendering/status, and preserve lifecycle-sensitive behavior such as cursor reset. Alternatives considered:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_decision_modal_module_returns_typed_effects_intents", "label": "Decision: Modal module returns typed effects/intents", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 35", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The modal module should accept current modal state, editor snapshot, input data, and options. It should return next modal state plus a small effect list that the adapter applies. Initial effect categories should cover current needs only: - delegate input to Pi"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_decision_keep_cursor_restoration_adapter_owned", "label": "Decision: Keep cursor restoration adapter-owned", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 50", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Programmatic edits can compute a target cursor in pure code, but reaching that cursor uses Pi public movement keys today. The modal module should return desired positions; the adapter should keep `setText()` plus public movement/restoration logic. Alternatives considered:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_decision_keep_parser_and_buffer_helpers_as_modal_dependencies", "label": "Decision: Keep parser and buffer helpers as modal dependencies", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 59", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "`src/commands.ts` should remain the finite normal-mode grammar. `src/buffer.ts` should remain the pure text/range/register layer. The modal module orchestrates those helpers and translates their results into effects. Alternatives considered:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_decision_separate_view_status_derivation_from_pi_rendering", "label": "Decision: Separate view/status derivation from Pi rendering", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 68", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Mode labels, pending labels, and visual summaries should become testable derivation helpers. The adapter should still call `super.render(width)` for non-visual rendering, use the existing visual render helper for active visual selections, and apply border/status formatting in the Pi-facing layer. Alternatives considered:"}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 77", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Effect model too broad \u2192 Keep union limited to current behavior; add variants only when a refactor slice needs them. - Behavior drift during extraction \u2192 Refactor in parity slices and run tests after each slice. - Pi shortcut regression \u2192 Preserve existing delegate/reset behavior and add modal tests for `Esc`, `Enter`, `Ctrl+C`, `Ctrl+D`, `Ctrl+G`, and unknown non-printable inputs."}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 86", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add modal state/effect/snapshot types without changing behavior. 2. Extract one mode path at a time from `VimEditor` into the modal module. 3. Keep `VimEditor` applying effects immediately after each extraction slice."}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_ref_src_commands_ts", "label": "commands.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_ref_src_buffer_ts", "label": "buffer.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_ref_src_index_ts", "label": "index.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_document", "target": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_document", "target": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_document", "target": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_decisions", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-05-27-deepen-vimeditor-pi-adapter-modal-editing-module/design.md", "source_location": "line 24", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_adapter_modal_editing_module_design_document", "target": "2026_05_27_deepen_vimeditor_pi_ad